                    It waits for the current update to fully complete (read, modify, write) before taking the next item from the queue.
                </p>
                <p>
                    This ensures that each increment operation starts with the most up-to-date count,
                    preventing any "reads" from stale data. This is a common pattern for managing
                    asynchronous operations that modify shared state, often implemented with techniques
                    like promises, async/await with locks (in environments that support them), or simple queues like this.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
