                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Click 1's <code>setTimeout</code> callback executes:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Sets <code>count</code> to <code>0 + 1 = 1</code>.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Click 2's <code>setTimeout</code> callback executes:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Sets <code>count</code> to <code>0 + 1 = 1</code>.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ol>
        <p>Even though you clicked twice, the counter only incremented once, because both operations started with the same initial value and overwrote each other's updates. The expected value would be 2.</p>

        <h3>Buggy Code Snippet:</h3>
        <pre><code>let buggyCount = 0;
