        <p>By chaining promises, we effectively serialize the asynchronous increment operations. Each operation waits for the one before it to finish, ensuring that when it reads <code>fixedCount</code>, it's reading the most up-to-date value. This prevents concurrent reads and writes from clashing and losing updates.</p>
